        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 1 at 5:59PM EDT until May 1 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
over Point Marion to near Farmington, or along a line from 8 miles
northeast of Star City to 7 miles southeast of Uniontown, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Uniontown, Masontown, Point Marion, Fairchance, Smithfield,
Nemacolin, New Salem, Greensboro, Chalkhill and Cheat Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
